race.comment: CHEWING GUM (5) has been frustrating for punters this time in, placing in all four runs, three of those as runner-up and a couple when beaten under half a length as favourite. She's drawn a touch awkwardly again but comes back a notch in grade and if she holds her form she can get the job done. TASSRON (4) resumes. He got over a bit more ground last time in, winning his maiden over 1500m two back before a fourth here over 1740m in a handy race. May find them a touch sharp but has the ability to be finishing strongly. ROCK THE BAR (1) resumes. He didn't fire in two runs last time in but his best would be very competitive. Watch the market for a lead. TIPSY GYPSY (9) is racing well in her first campaign and has claims again despite a wide draw.
